abstract: There are many pitfalls on the road ahead.
snippet: There are many pitfalls on the road ahead.
lead_paragraph: On Monday night, the Iowa caucuses ended in chaos. More important, the partial results released on Tuesday suggest that the Democratic path to the White House remains rocky.

headline_main: If Bernie Wins, Where Will He Take the Democratic Party?

abstract: Why should we listen to her anyway? Remember when she fell for Rick Santorum?
snippet: Why should we listen to her anyway? Remember when she fell for Rick Santorum?
lead_paragraph: There we were, at the pot luck at Iowa’s farmhouse. Virginia brought a Smithfield ham. Pennsylvania brought scrapple. Kentucky brought some bourbon. As for me — the Pine Tree State — I brought lobster, of course. They used to say, as goes me, so goes the nation. But to be honest, this hasn’t been true for decades.

abstract: Iowa Democrats were drawn to two faces of change.
snippet: Iowa Democrats were drawn to two faces of change.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Iowa Democrats were drawn to two faces of change.
headline_main: Analysis: Iowa Democrats Drawn to Two Faces of Change
headline_print_headline: Analysis: Iowa Democrats Drawn to Two Faces of Change

abstract: WASHINGTON — New Iowa caucus results released late Tuesday night showed Pete Buttigieg continuing to lead the Democratic field, just ahead of Senator Bernie Sanders. Senator Elizabeth Warren remained in third place, and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. was a distant fourth. Seventy-one percent of precincts have now reported results.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — New Iowa caucus results released late Tuesday night showed Pete Buttigieg continuing to lead the Democratic field, just ahead of Senator Bernie Sanders. Senator Elizabeth Warren remained in third place, and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. was a distant fourth. Seventy-one percent of precincts have now reported results.
headline_main: New Iowa results still show Buttigieg with a narrow lead.

headline_main: ‘It validates things’: Buttigieg supporters are heartened in New Hampshire.

abstract: Buttigieg and Sanders were triumphant. But Trump had a few things he wanted to say for himself.
snippet: Buttigieg and Sanders were triumphant. But Trump had a few things he wanted to say for himself.
lead_paragraph: Bret Stephens: Just when I thought the Iowa caucus, and maybe the Democratic nomination, was in the bag for Bernie Sanders, Pete Buttigieg pulled out what looks to be either a largely unpredicted first-place finish in the Hawkeye State or at least a close second-place.

abstract: Facing questions about his campaign's viability, Joe Biden escalated his criticism of his top Democratic rivals on Wednesday, suggesting both Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg were risky choices for a party desperate for a return to the White House.
snippet: Facing questions about his campaign's viability, Joe Biden escalated his criticism of his top Democratic rivals on Wednesday, suggesting both Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg were risky choices for a party desperate for a return to the White Hous...
lead_paragraph: SOMERSWORTH, N.H. — Facing questions about his campaign's viability, Joe Biden escalated his criticism of his top Democratic rivals on Wednesday, suggesting both Bernie Sanders and Pete Buttigieg were risky choices for a party desperate for a return to the White House.
headline_main: Biden Casts Top Rivals as a Risk for Party That Wants to Win
headline_print_headline: Biden Casts Top Rivals as a Risk for Party That Wants to Win

abstract: On the eve of the final Senate votes in the impeachment trial, President Trump traded snubs with Speaker Nancy Pelosi and promoted a ‘Great American Comeback,’ pausing to award Rush Limbaugh the Presidential Medal of Freedom.
snippet: On the eve of the final Senate votes in the impeachment trial, President Trump traded snubs with Speaker Nancy Pelosi and promoted a ‘Great American Comeback,’ pausing to award Rush Limbaugh the Presidential Medal of Freedom.
lead_paragraph: With the November election just nine months away, President Trump used his speech to frame the choice as he sees it, claiming credit for what he called a “Great American Comeback” and revival of American spirit while defining the coming campaign against the Democrats as a battle to stop the rise of socialism in the United States.
headline_main: State of the Union Updates: Trump Adds Reality Show Flourishes to Address
